1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with graph theory and the concept of equivalence relations on the edge set of a graph, which falls under the purview of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the computation of RSP-relations, which involves algorithmic techniques and data structures. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The concept of graph products and their properties are relevant to game theory and social network analysis, which are sub-fields of computer science. 
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the construction of covering graphs, which is a topic of interest in computational geometry. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper's focus on graph bundles and their properties is relevant to the study of social and information networks.
